                    ' after getting credentials metadata. Retrying pick'
                );
                this.doPick();
                return;`

do pick keeps re-invoking endlessly - causing the application to freeze.

if it help in any way, we are using the following code to connect to the stream:
`async connectToStream(): Promise<void> {
    if (this.subscribeReqId) {
      throw new Error('stream init already in progress');
    }

    await ensureConnectivityState(this.client);

    log.debug('connecting to connect ui stream');

    if (this.stream) {
      this.stream.removeAllListeners();
      this.stream = undefined;
    }

    this.stream = this.buildStream();

    log.debug('subscribeToConnectUiStream');
    this.subscribeToStreamHooks();

    this.subscribeReqId = this.generateRandomRequestId();
    try {
      const res = await new Promise<TRes>((resolve, reject) => {
        const subscriptionRequest = this.buildSubscribeMessage(this.subscribeReqId);
        this.stream.write(subscriptionRequest);
        this.responseCache.set(this.subscribeReqId, {resolve, reject}, this.defualtRequestTimeout);

        log.debug('connected to service stream');
      });

      this.handleStreamSubscriptionResponse(res);
    } finally {
      this.subscribeReqId = undefined;
    }

    this.isStreamConnected = true;
  }`

the line `log.debug('connected to service stream');` is the last one that's been executed before the app freeze and enter the endless recursion loop.
 
### Reproduction steps
Unfortunately that's not easy  to reproduce this happens 1 to every 10-20 that I reset the service killing the stream. I guess that it happens in some weird state of the stream.  

